  "body": "Steps to reproduce:\r\n1. Sync to mainnet to at least block 800k\r\n2. Note the location of the chaindata file\r\n3. Choose the location of the state file\r\n3. Build `state` command line tool\r\n4. Make sure that the state file does not exist (remove it if you are re-running the reproduction)\r\n5. Run this command `./build/bin/state -action stateless -chaindata <your_chaindata> -statefile <your_state_file> -triesize 50000`\r\n6. Wait until it prints similar to the following and terminates:\r\n````\r\nINFO [11-07|10:51:04.496] Memory                                   nodes=49979 alloc=289806 sys=1596180 numGC=2005\r\nProcessed 791000 blocks\r\nFailed to resolve state trie: mismatching hash: <138fcb4de028a37c8a47c578f5afb2caadf246fc39879d822f77749081346109>  9e36c35ff2ac9246739cab5f12e2f06a51bcad9f7b8b259e4\r\n739465eaed7131d for prefix d83656e6b88e9d59401dc85aa80b7102c19b40dd4f78a49585f748f822783f37ffffffffffffffff, resolveHex 080b0d04060303030107090d0e0006090d0b0007010e0\r\nf070e02060d0c030f0605060c04000e000d0306060501020d05030502040d060b070b0103030e08060c10, resolvePos 4\r\nINFO [11-07|10:51:05.598] Database closed                          database=/mnt/disks/nvme/geth/chaindata\r\n````\r\n\r\nThe error is printed by this line: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/blob/c9e1cb8b7728d7d302cf192512fa6614e2584cbe/cmd/state/stateless.go#L206",
